All Implemented Interfaces:
ClementiniGeometry, Cloneable, Externalizable, FeatureGeometry, Geometry, GeometryCollection, HitTest, PointApplicatorUser, Polygon, SegmentHitTest, Serializable, Shape
public class BasePolygon
extends BaseFeatureGeometry
implements Polygon, Externalizable

This class implements a polygon object. A polygon contains multiple rings. It may also contain multiple interior and exterior rings. This class contains two sets of methods for creating polygons. When you know the ring relationships, use BasePolygon(size), setExteriorRing(), and setInteriorRing() to construct the polygon. When the ring relationships are not known, use BasePolygon(rings) method to construct the polygon.

BasePolygon

public BasePolygon(Ring[] rings,
                   boolean isShapeFile)
Constructs a new Polygon with the given array of rings. If the rings come from a shapefile, then you can use the faster, shapefile based agorithm to determine the relationships between rings. If you are unsure, use the slower, more general algorithm.

Parameters:
rings - the ring array used to create this Polygon
isShapeFile - Determines which algorithm is used to build the relationship between rings. true = use the faster, shapefile based algorithm

public Envelope getEnvelopeByRef()

Determines the bounding box of the geometry. This method returns a reference to an existing envelope.

This method is provided to reduce memory consumption and should be used with care. Modifications should not be made to the returned envelope. Implementing classes are free to return an actual reference or a completely new object providing it is stated in the method's documentation.

buffer

public final Polygon buffer(double bufferDistance,
                            double minOrdDistance)
This method generates the outer shell of a feature geometry. No donut holes are created. It assumes that the feature is valid, that means the order of the points is in CCW mode for polygons, and that there are no repeated or duplicate points.

NOTE: This method buffers the exterior rings only

Specified by:
buffer in interface FeatureGeometry
Parameters:
bufferDistance - the buffer distance
minOrdDistance - the maximum deviation allowed from the generated chords to the conceptual circular curve. the mid-ordinant distance is the maximum distance from a chord with its endpoints on the curve to the curve itself.
Returns:
the buffer polygon
See Also:
InvalidDistanceException
